	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You can't.  The Gameboy hardware is inside the cartridge, it just uses the SNES for video, controller, and sound pass-through.  Gameboy emulators should have a Super Gameboy mode.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


