	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The way to correctly emulate a Super Game Boy: <ol style="list-style-type: decimal"><li>Start with a Game Boy emulator and a Super NES emulator. </li><li>Separate each emulator's backend (which takes a ROM image and a key state and produces video and audio) from its frontend (which relays these to and from the operating system). </li><li>Have the Super NES backend act as a frontend to the Game Boy backend when the Super Game Boy ROM is run. </li></ol>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


